README.md
     1â†’# MCPHost SDK
     3â†’The MCPHost SDK allows you to use MCPHost programmatically from Go applications without spawning OS processes.
     4â†’
     5â†’## Installation
     7â†’```bash
     8â†’go get github.com/mark3labs/mcphost
     9â†’```
    10â†’
    11â†’## Basic Usage
    13â†’```go
    14â†’package main
    15â†’
    16â†’import (
    17â†’    "context"
    18â†’    "fmt"
    19â†’    "log"
    20â†’    
    21â†’    "github.com/mark3labs/mcphost/sdk"
    22â†’)
    23â†’
    24â†’func main() {
    25â†’    ctx := context.Background()
    26â†’    
    27â†’    // Create MCPHost instance with default configuration
    28â†’    host, err := sdk.New(ctx, nil)
    29â†’    if err != nil {
    30â†’        log.Fatal(err)
    31â†’    }
    32â†’    defer host.Close()
    33â†’    
    34â†’    // Send a prompt
    35â†’    response, err := host.Prompt(ctx, "What is 2+2?")
    36â†’    if err != nil {
    37â†’        log.Fatal(err)
    38â†’    }
    39â†’    
    40â†’    fmt.Println(response)
    41â†’}
    42â†’```
    43â†’
    44â†’## Configuration
    46â†’The SDK behaves identically to the CLI:
    47â†’- Loads configuration from `~/.mcphost.yml` by default
    48â†’- Creates default configuration if none exists
    49â†’- Respects all environment variables (`MCPHOST_*`)
    50â†’- Uses the same defaults as the CLI
    51â†’
    52â†’### Options
    54â†’You can override specific settings:
    55â†’
    56â†’```go
    57â†’host, err := sdk.New(ctx, &sdk.Options{
    58â†’    Model:        "ollama:llama3",           // Override model
    59â†’    SystemPrompt: "You are a helpful bot",   // Override system prompt
    60â†’    ConfigFile:   "/path/to/config.yml",     // Use specific config file
    61â†’    MaxSteps:     10,                        // Override max steps
    62â†’    Streaming:    true,                      // Enable streaming
    63â†’    Quiet:        true,                      // Suppress debug output
    64â†’})
    65â†’```
